# ü™® Falling Rocks Game ‚Äì Tutorial for Kids!

Welcome! In this tutorial, you are going to build a **falling rocks game** using **MakeCode Arcade**. You will control a character that catches yummy burgers, dodges dangerous rocks, and grabs special power-ups to slow everything down. Let's go! üéÆ

---

## üß∞ What You Need

- A computer or tablet
- Go to **[MakeCode Arcade](https://arcade.makecode.com)** in your web browser
- Click **"New Project"** and give it a fun name like "Falling Rocks!"
- Click the **JavaScript** tab at the top so you can type code

---

## üóÇÔ∏è Table of Contents

1. Set Up the Screen
2. Create Your Player
3. Make Rocks Fall
4. Make Burgers Fall
5. Make Power-Ups Appear
6. What Happens When Things Collide
7. Make the Game Get Harder Over Time
8. The Slow Rocks Power (a Special Function)

---

## Step 1 ‚Äì Set Up the Screen üñ•Ô∏è

This is the very first thing we do. We tell the game what color the background should be, and we get our score and lives ready.

```javascript
scene.setBackgroundColor(1)
info.setLife(3)
info.setScore(0)
```

**What this does:**
- `setBackgroundColor(1)` paints the background **dark blue** (color number 1).
- `setLife(3)` gives your player **3 hearts** (lives) before game over.
- `setScore(0)` starts your score at **zero**.

---

## Step 2 ‚Äì Create Your Player üßç

Now we make the little character you will control! The big block of letters and dots between the backticks is a **pixel drawing** of your character. MakeCode turns it into a picture automatically.

```javascript
let playerSprite = sprites.create(img`
    ........................
    .....ffff...............
    ...fff22fff.............
    ..fff2222fff............
    .fffeeeeeefff...........
    .ffe222222eef...........
    .fe2ffffff2ef...........
    .ffffeeeeffff...........
    ffefbf44fbfeff..........
    fee41fddf14eef..........
    .ffffdddddeef...........
    fddddf444eef............
    fbbbbf2222f4e...........
    fbbbbf2222fd4...........
    .fccf45544f44...........
    ..ffffffff..............
    ....ff..ff..............
    ........................
    `, SpriteKind.Player)

controller.moveSprite(playerSprite, 120, 0)
playerSprite.setFlag(SpriteFlag.StayInScreen, true)
playerSprite.y = 110
```

**What this does:**
- `sprites.create(...)` draws your character on the screen.
- `SpriteKind.Player` tells the game **"this is the player!"**
- `controller.moveSprite(playerSprite, 120, 0)` lets you move the player **left and right** using the arrow keys. The `120` is how fast they move. The `0` means they can't move up or down.
- `StayInScreen` makes sure your player **never walks off the edge** of the screen.
- `playerSprite.y = 110` places your player **near the bottom** of the screen so falling things can land on them.

---

## Step 3 ‚Äì Make Rocks Fall ü™®

Rocks are the **enemies**! They fall from the top of the screen and you need to dodge them.

```javascript
let fallSpeed = 40
let spawnTime = 800

game.onUpdateInterval(spawnTime, function () {
    rock = sprites.create(img`
        . . c c c c . . 
        . c b d d d c . 
        c b d d d d d c 
        c b b d d d d c 
        c b d b d d b c 
        c c b d b b b c 
        c c c b d d b c 
        c c b b c c c c 
        `, SpriteKind.Enemy)
    rock.x = randint(10, 150)
    rock.y = 0
    rock.vy = randint(fallSpeed, fallSpeed + 40)
    rock.setFlag(SpriteFlag.AutoDestroy, true)
})
```

**What this does:**
- `game.onUpdateInterval(spawnTime, ...)` runs the code inside every **800 milliseconds** (less than 1 second!). Every time it runs, a new rock appears.
- `rock.x = randint(10, 150)` puts the rock at a **random spot** across the screen so you never know where it will come from.
- `rock.y = 0` starts the rock at the **very top** of the screen.
- `rock.vy = randint(fallSpeed, fallSpeed + 40)` makes the rock fall downward. A bigger number means **faster**!
- `AutoDestroy` means the rock disappears on its own if it falls off the bottom, so the game doesn't slow down.

---

## Step 4 ‚Äì Make Burgers Fall üçî

Burgers are the **good things** to catch! Each one gives you a point.

```javascript
game.onUpdateInterval(2000, function () {
    burger = sprites.create(img`
        . . . . c c c b b b b b . . . . 
        . . c c b 4 4 4 4 4 4 b b b . . 
        . c c 4 4 4 4 4 5 4 4 4 4 b c . 
        . e 4 4 4 4 4 4 4 4 4 5 4 4 e . 
        e b 4 5 4 4 5 4 4 4 4 4 4 4 b c 
        e b 4 4 4 4 4 4 4 4 4 4 5 4 4 e 
        e b b 4 4 4 4 4 4 4 4 4 4 4 b e 
        . e b 4 4 4 4 4 5 4 4 4 4 b e . 
        8 7 e e b 4 4 4 4 4 4 b e e 6 8 
        8 7 2 e e e e e e e e e e 2 7 8 
        e 6 6 2 2 2 2 2 2 2 2 2 2 6 c e 
        e c 6 7 6 6 7 7 7 6 6 7 6 c c e 
        e b e 8 8 c c 8 8 c c c 8 e b e 
        e e b e c c e e e e e c e b e e 
        . e e b b 4 4 4 4 4 4 4 4 e e . 
        . . . c c c c c e e e e e . . . 
        `, SpriteKind.Food)
    burger.x = randint(10, 150)
    burger.y = 0
    burger.vy = randint(30, 60)
    burger.setFlag(SpriteFlag.AutoDestroy, true)
})
```

**What this does:**
- A new burger appears every **2 seconds**.
- Just like rocks, burgers fall from a random spot at the top.
- `SpriteKind.Food` tells the game these are the good guys!

---

## Step 5 ‚Äì Make Power-Ups Appear ‚≠ê

Power-ups are **rare and special**. They only appear every 15 seconds! If you catch one, you get an extra life AND all the rocks slow down for 3 seconds.

```javascript
game.onUpdateInterval(15000, function () {
    powerup = sprites.create(img`
        . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 
        . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 
        . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 
        . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 
        . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 
        . . . . . . . 2 2 . . . . . . . 
        . . . . . . 3 1 1 3 . . . . . . 
        . . . . . 2 1 1 1 1 2 . . . . . 
        . . . . . 2 1 1 1 1 2 . . . . . 
        . . . . . . 3 1 1 3 . . . . . . 
        . . . . . . . 2 2 . . . . . . . 
        . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 
        . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 
        . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 
        . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 
        . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . 
        `, SpriteKind.PowerUp)
    powerup.x = randint(10, 150)
    powerup.y = 0
    powerup.vy = randint(30, 50)
    powerup.setFlag(SpriteFlag.AutoDestroy, true)
})
```

**What this does:**
- Every **15 seconds**, a shiny power-up drops from the top.
- It works just like rocks and burgers ‚Äì random position, falls down, disappears at the bottom.
- `SpriteKind.PowerUp` is a **brand new kind** of sprite we created specially for this game.

---

## Step 6 ‚Äì What Happens When Things Touch (Collisions!) üí•

This is the exciting part! We tell the game what to do when your player **touches** different things.

### üçî Catching a Burger

```javascript
sprites.onOverlap(SpriteKind.Player, SpriteKind.Food, function (sprite, otherSprite) {
    otherSprite.destroy(effects.hearts, 100)
    info.changeScoreBy(1)
})
```

- When your player touches a burger, the burger **disappears with a hearts effect** üíó.
- Your score goes **up by 1**.

### ‚≠ê Catching a Power-Up

```javascript
sprites.onOverlap(SpriteKind.Player, SpriteKind.PowerUp, function (sprite, otherSprite) {
    otherSprite.destroy(effects.smiles, 100)
    info.changeLifeBy(1)
    slowRocks(3000)
})
```

- The power-up disappears with a **smiley face effect** üòä.
- You gain **+1 life** (heart).
- The special `slowRocks` function runs for **3 seconds**!

### ü™® Getting Hit by a Rock

```javascript
sprites.onOverlap(SpriteKind.Player, SpriteKind.Enemy, function (sprite, otherSprite) {
    otherSprite.destroy(effects.disintegrate, 200)
    info.changeLifeBy(-1)
    pause(200)
    if (info.life() <= 0) {
        game.over(false, effects.melt)
    }
})
```

- The rock **shatters** with a cool disintegrate effect.
- You lose **-1 life** üíî.
- After a tiny pause, the game checks: **do you have 0 lives left?**
- If yes ‚Üí **Game Over!** with a melting effect. üò¢

---

## Step 7 ‚Äì Make the Game Get Harder Over Time üìà

Games are more fun when they get trickier! Every 10 seconds, rocks fall faster AND appear more often.

```javascript
game.onUpdateInterval(10000, function () {
    fallSpeed += 10
    if (spawnTime > 300) {
        spawnTime += -100
    }
})
```

**What this does:**
- `fallSpeed += 10` makes every new rock fall **10 units faster** than before.
- `spawnTime += -100` makes rocks appear **100 milliseconds sooner** each time. So instead of every 800ms, it becomes 700ms, then 600ms‚Ä¶ all the way down to 300ms! That's super fast! üöÄ
- The `if (spawnTime > 300)` check makes sure the game **never gets impossibly fast** ‚Äì 300ms is the speed limit.

---

## Step 8 ‚Äì The Slow Rocks Power ‚ùÑÔ∏è (A Special Function)

This is a **function** ‚Äì think of it like a helper robot you can call whenever you need it. This one slows down all rocks for a little while.

```javascript
function slowRocks(duration: number) {
    enemies = sprites.allOfKind(SpriteKind.Enemy)
    originalSpeeds = []
    for (let s of enemies) {
        originalSpeeds.push(s.vy)
        s.vy = Math.max(10, s.vy / 2)
    }
    pause(duration)
    for (let i = 0; i <= enemies.length - 1; i++) {
        if (i < originalSpeeds.length) {
            enemies[i].vy = originalSpeeds[i]
        }
    }
}
```

**What this does, step by step:**
1. `sprites.allOfKind(SpriteKind.Enemy)` finds **every rock** currently on the screen.
2. We **remember how fast** each rock was going by saving the speeds in a list called `originalSpeeds`.
3. We then **cut each rock's speed in half** (`s.vy / 2`). `Math.max(10, ...)` makes sure no rock goes slower than 10 ‚Äì otherwise it might just stop completely!
4. `pause(duration)` waits for **3 seconds** (3000 milliseconds) while the rocks are slow.
5. After the pause, we **give every rock its old speed back** so the game returns to normal.

---

## üéâ You Did It!

Here's a quick recap of everything in your game:

| Thing | What it does |
|---|---|
| üßç Player | You! Move left and right to dodge and catch things |
| ü™® Rock (Enemy) | Avoid these! You lose a life if hit |
| üçî Burger (Food) | Catch these! You earn a point |
| ‚≠ê Power-Up | Catch these! Get a life + slow all rocks for 3 seconds |
| üìà Difficulty | Every 10 seconds, rocks fall faster and more often |

